'''Ancylopoda''' is a group of browsing, [[herbivorous]], [[mammal]]s in the [[Perissodactyla]] that show long, curved and cleft [[claw]]s.<ref>{{cite journal
  | last = Coombs
  | first = Margery C.  
  | coauthors = Rothschild, Bruce M.
  | title = Phalangeal Fusion in Schizotheriine Chalicotheres (Mammalia, Perissodactyla)
  | journal = Journal of Paleontology
  | volume = 73
  | issue = 4
  | pages = 682â€“690
  | publisher = Paleontological Society
  | date = Jul 1999
  | jstor = 1306767
  | doi =
  | accessdate = 2009-12-31}}</ref> [[Morphology (biology)|Morphological]] evidence indicates the Ancylopoda diverged from the [[tapir]]s, [[rhinoceros]]es and [[horse]]s ([[Euperissodactyla]]) after the Brontotheria, however earlier authorities such as [[Osborn]]{{disambiguation needed|date=November 2012}} sometimes considered the Ancylopoda to be outside Perissodactyla or, as was popular more recently,  to be related to [[Brontotheria]].

